<div id="oujwjq8iqkvn7uwo1rq6" data-disable-jsonld="true" data-volume="70" data-ratio="16:9"></div>
<script data-cfasync="false" src="/cdn-cgi/scripts/5c5dd728/cloudflare-static/email-decode.min.js"></script><script type="text/javascript" src="//video.mediavine.com/videos/oujwjq8iqkvn7uwo1rq6.js" async="" data-noptimize=""></script>



<p class="p1"><span class="s1">If you&rsquo;re looking for a quick, simple, delicious cake to serve and snack on this summer, you&rsquo;ve come to the right place!</span></p>



<p class="p1"><span class="s1">No bells and whistles (or frosting and filling) on this one. Just the season&rsquo;s best fresh sweet cherries, simple pantry ingredients, half an hour in the oven, done.</span></p>



<p class="p1"><span class="s1">This cherry cake from scratch goes so well with your morning coffee, great for picnics and is perfect with ice cream.</span></p>



<span id="more-5546"></span>



<h2 class="p1 wp-block-heading"><span id="How_to_make_this_easy_cherry_cake_recipe"><span class="s1">How to make this easy cherry cake recipe</span></span></h2>


<div class="wp-block-image">
<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="450" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;680&#039;%20height=&#039;450&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20680%20450&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Easy Cherry Cake Recipe from Scratch" class="wp-image-5553 perfmatters-lazy" data-pin-media="https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-2.jpg" data-src="https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-2.jpg" data-srcset="https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-2.jpg 680w, https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-2-300x199.jpg 300w" data-sizes="auto, (max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure></div>


<p class="p1"><span class="s1">To make this homemade cherry cake, you start by sifting flour with baking powder and salt. You set that aside while you cream butter and sugar until fluffy and light.</span></p>



<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Then in goes the egg, buttermilk and vanilla. Mix until incorporated. Gradually add your flour mixture and stir until just combined. </span></p>



<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Transfer the batter into your prepared pan and place cherries on top. Bake for 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the centre comes out clean.</span></p>



<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Allow the cake to cool in the pan on a wire rack. Sprinkle some powdered sugar or top with ice cream and enjoy!</span></p>



<h2 class="p1 wp-block-heading"><span id="Ingredients"><span class="s1">Ingredients</span></span></h2>



<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Like I said earlier, there are no hard-to-source ingredients in this easy cherry cake recipe. All you need are the following pantry staples:</span></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><span class="s1"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B005EOTMA6/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;creativeASIN=B005EOTMA6&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=theunlbak-20&amp;linkId=b72963fecce3dce092e5dcf4f08da28d" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener sponsored nofollow">All-purpose flour</a><img decoding="async" width="1" height="1" border="0" style="border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1&#039;%20height=&#039;1&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201%201&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt data-pin-media="//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=theunlbak-20&amp;l=am2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B005EOTMA6" class="perfmatters-lazy" data-src="//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=theunlbak-20&amp;l=am2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B005EOTMA6" /></span></li>



<li><span class="s1"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B000VK7PG6/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;creativeASIN=B000VK7PG6&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=theunlbak-20&amp;linkId=68f38ba2e57d14177b1e1081273e20de" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener sponsored nofollow">Baking powder</a><img decoding="async" width="1" height="1" border="0" style="border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1&#039;%20height=&#039;1&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201%201&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt data-pin-media="//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=theunlbak-20&amp;l=am2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B000VK7PG6" class="perfmatters-lazy" data-src="//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=theunlbak-20&amp;l=am2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B000VK7PG6" /></span></li>



<li><span class="s1">Salt</span></li>



<li><span class="s1">Unsalted butter</span></li>



<li><span class="s1"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00060N5OW/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;creativeASIN=B00060N5OW&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=theunlbak-20&amp;linkId=707ca375e0fe32880787cc605588a06d" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener sponsored nofollow">Granulated sugar</a><img decoding="async" width="1" height="1" border="0" style="border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1&#039;%20height=&#039;1&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201%201&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt data-pin-media="//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=theunlbak-20&amp;l=am2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B00060N5OW" class="perfmatters-lazy" data-src="//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=theunlbak-20&amp;l=am2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B00060N5OW" /></span></li>



<li><span class="s1">Egg</span></li>



<li><span class="s1">Buttermilk</span></li>



<li><span class="s1"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B0000VLU1W/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;creativeASIN=B0000VLU1W&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=theunlbak-20&amp;linkId=48e89d7cecfa4915961d716dc218fd64" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener sponsored nofollow">Vanilla extract</a><img decoding="async" width="1" height="1" border="0" style="border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1&#039;%20height=&#039;1&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201%201&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt data-pin-media="//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=theunlbak-20&amp;l=am2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B0000VLU1W" class="perfmatters-lazy" data-src="//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=theunlbak-20&amp;l=am2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B0000VLU1W" /></span></li>



<li><span class="s1">Cherries</span></li>
</ul>



<h2 class="p1 wp-block-heading"><span id="Baking_tools"><span class="s1">Baking tools</span></span></h2>



<p class="p1"><span class="s1">You don&rsquo;t need special tools either. I like using my <a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B003OXNBYC/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;creativeASIN=B003OXNBYC&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=theunlbak-20&amp;linkId=eda102975f409cba2fa31c7c94159821" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener sponsored nofollow">stand mixer</a><img decoding="async" width="1" height="1" border="0" style="border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1&#039;%20height=&#039;1&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201%201&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt data-pin-media="//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=theunlbak-20&amp;l=am2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B003OXNBYC" class="perfmatters-lazy" data-src="//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=theunlbak-20&amp;l=am2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B003OXNBYC" /> but a large bowl + a <a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B009VUHLHA/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;creativeASIN=B009VUHLHA&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=theunlbak-20&amp;linkId=b4be4250ea0c966cf9f4c3023be344d4" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener sponsored nofollow">handheld electric mixer</a><img decoding="async" width="1" height="1" border="0" style="border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1&#039;%20height=&#039;1&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201%201&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt data-pin-media="//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=theunlbak-20&amp;l=am2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B009VUHLHA" class="perfmatters-lazy" data-src="//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=theunlbak-20&amp;l=am2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B009VUHLHA" /> would work just as well too. </span></p>



<p class="p1"><span class="s1">In addition, you need:</span></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><span class="s1">A <a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B002UNMZO4/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;creativeASIN=B002UNMZO4&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=theunlbak-20&amp;linkId=cbd826b8dc4727d326338265851873a6" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener sponsored nofollow">9&times;9 inch baking pan</a><img decoding="async" width="1" height="1" border="0" style="border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1&#039;%20height=&#039;1&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201%201&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt data-pin-media="//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=theunlbak-20&amp;l=am2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B002UNMZO4" class="perfmatters-lazy" data-src="//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=theunlbak-20&amp;l=am2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B002UNMZO4" /></span></li>



<li><span class="s1"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B006JCWGIC/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;creativeASIN=B006JCWGIC&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=theunlbak-20&amp;linkId=ee51895a89b0bcb6a6aaf1ccdec1ba7a" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener sponsored nofollow">Parchment paper</a><img decoding="async" width="1" height="1" border="0" style="border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1&#039;%20height=&#039;1&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201%201&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt data-pin-media="//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=theunlbak-20&amp;l=am2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B006JCWGIC" class="perfmatters-lazy" data-src="//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=theunlbak-20&amp;l=am2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B006JCWGIC" /></span></li>



<li><span class="s1">Spatula</span></li>



<li><span class="s1"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B078Y316M5/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;creativeASIN=B078Y316M5&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=theunlbak-20&amp;linkId=44aa7d67045ebc881f2272f9cc78b1df" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener sponsored nofollow">Cooling rack</a><img decoding="async" width="1" height="1" border="0" style="border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1&#039;%20height=&#039;1&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201%201&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt data-pin-media="//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=theunlbak-20&amp;l=am2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B078Y316M5" class="perfmatters-lazy" data-src="//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=theunlbak-20&amp;l=am2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B078Y316M5" /></span></li>
</ul>



<p class="p1"><span class="s1">I like using a <a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00004OCNJ/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;creativeASIN=B00004OCNJ&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=theunlbak-20&amp;linkId=d215c1c800b48e99578397bfcf6cd543" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener sponsored nofollow">bench scraper</a><img decoding="async" width="1" height="1" border="0" style="border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1&#039;%20height=&#039;1&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201%201&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt data-pin-media="//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=theunlbak-20&amp;l=am2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B00004OCNJ" class="perfmatters-lazy" data-src="//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=theunlbak-20&amp;l=am2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B00004OCNJ" /> to cut sheet cakes but a knife will do too.</span></p>



<h2 class="p1 wp-block-heading"><span id="Recipe_FAQs"><span class="s1">Recipe FAQs</span></span></h2>


<div class="wp-block-image">
<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="900" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;680&#039;%20height=&#039;900&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20680%20900&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Easy Cherry Cake Recipe from Scratch" class="wp-image-5555 perfmatters-lazy" data-pin-media="https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-4.jpg" data-src="https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-4.jpg" data-srcset="https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-4.jpg 680w, https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-4-227x300.jpg 227w" data-sizes="auto, (max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure></div>


<p class="p1"><span class="s1">To make this super easy recipe for cherry cake even easier, here are some tips for you.</span></p>



<div class="schema-faq wp-block-yoast-faq-block"><div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1659030405895"><strong class="schema-faq-question">How to make homemade buttermilk</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer"><br>This recipe only needs ½ cup of buttermilk and if you&rsquo;re like me and can only buy it in 1L bottles, you need to plan out your week and make all things buttermilk (here&rsquo;s a great <a href="https://theunlikelybaker.com/ways-to-use-leftover-buttermilk/"><strong>collection of recipes to help you use that leftover buttermilk</strong></a>).<br><br>Or, you can make buttermilk at home so you have just the right amount you need.<br>It&rsquo;s so simple: I just mix a cup of milk and a tablespoon of lemon juice, stir then let it sit in room temperature for 30 minutes.<br><br>Homemade buttermilk doesn&rsquo;t get quite as thick as the one you buy at the store though. Good news is I haven&rsquo;t noticed a significant difference in my baking yet. So I don&rsquo;t hesitate to make homemade buttermilk in a pinch.<br><br>Here&rsquo;s an interesting read on <a href="https://www.thekitchn.com/is-there-a-difference-between-commercial-homemade-buttermilk-223086" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">commercial vs. homemade buttermilk</a>, if you&rsquo;re curious.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1659030435574"><strong class="schema-faq-question">How to pit cherries without a cherry pitter</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer"><br>I love cherries &ndash; eating them fresh and baking with them (or making <a href="https://theunlikelybaker.com/roasted-cherry-choco-chip-ice-cream-video/"><strong>homemade roasted</strong> <strong>cherry chocolate ice cream</strong></a> &ndash; so good!).<br><br>Over the years (and countless days of cherry red hands later) I&rsquo;ve realized that a <a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B008FWD4HQ/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;creativeASIN=B008FWD4HQ&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=theunlbak-20&amp;linkId=7c16b99c18cee28d974358e845d6aef0" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener sponsored nofollow">cherry pitter</a><img decoding="async" width="1" height="1" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;1&#039;%20height=&#039;1&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%201%201&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt data-pin-media="//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=theunlbak-20&amp;l=am2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B008FWD4HQ" class="perfmatters-lazy" data-src="//ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=theunlbak-20&amp;l=am2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B008FWD4HQ" /> might be one of the best inventions of mankind ever.<br><br>Invest in one and you won&rsquo;t look back.<br><br>If you don&rsquo;t have one though, there are many ways to pit a cherry. From using a straw (didn&rsquo;t work for me) to using a paper clip (this one hurt!). Here&rsquo;s one <a href="https://www.kitchentreaty.com/the-easiest-way-to-pit-a-cherry-without-a-pitter/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener sponsored nofollow">using a piping/icing tip</a> (I haven&rsquo;t tried this but it looks very promising).<br><br>See what method works best for you (or invest in a pitter already!).</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1659030467259"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Can I use frozen cherries for this recipe?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer"><br>If you want to avoid all that drama altogether, you might be wondering if you can just use frozen cherries for this recipe. The answer is you can.<br><br>When cherries are $1 a basket, we tend to <del>hoard</del> buy more than normal people would and freeze them ourselves so we can have cherry parties all year.<br><br>When the craving hits and I want to bake cherry cake from scratch, I simply thaw them in the fridge. <br><br>I just make sure to remove any excess moisture before I use them so my cake doesn&rsquo;t end up being too mushy.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1659030508154"><strong class="schema-faq-question">How do I store this cake?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer"><br>You can store this cherry buttermilk cake in an airtight container in the fridge. It will be good for up to 2 days.<br><br>We like eating this cake chilled too so we don&rsquo;t usually bring it down to room temperature before serving.</p> </div> </div>



<h2 class="p1 wp-block-heading"><span id="Other_cake_recipes_that_are_easy_to_make_from_scratch"><span class="s1">Other cake recipes that are easy to make from scratch</span></span></h2>



<p class="p1"><span class="s1">If there are no cherries available there yet or &ndash; gasp &ndash; you missed cherry season, here are other cakes you can bake that are just as easy and delicious. </span></p>



<p class="p1"><span class="s1">This <a href="https://theunlikelybaker.com/sour-cream-peach-cake/"><b>sour cream peach cake</b></a> also uses a favourite summer fruit. Delicious, fruity, will definitely give you all the summer feels.</span></p>


<div class="wp-block-image">
<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="900" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;680&#039;%20height=&#039;900&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20680%20900&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Sour Cream Peach Cake - Made with Fresh Peaches!" class="wp-image-5456 perfmatters-lazy" data-pin-media="https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Sour-Cream-Peach-Cake-1.jpg" data-src="https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Sour-Cream-Peach-Cake-1.jpg" data-srcset="https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Sour-Cream-Peach-Cake-1.jpg 680w, https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Sour-Cream-Peach-Cake-1-227x300.jpg 227w" data-sizes="auto, (max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure></div>


<p class="p1"><span class="s1">It can&rsquo;t get any simpler than this <a href="https://theunlikelybaker.com/easy-yogurt-cake-strawberries-cream/"><b>easy yogurt cake</b></a>. Top it with fresh strawberries (or your favourite berry) and cream for a fantastic summer dessert.</span></p>


<div class="wp-block-image">
<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="900" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;680&#039;%20height=&#039;900&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20680%20900&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Easy Yogurt Cake with Strawberries and Cream" class="wp-image-4139 perfmatters-lazy" data-pin-media="https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Easy-Yogurt-Cake-Strawberries-and-Cream-1.jpg" data-src="https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Easy-Yogurt-Cake-Strawberries-and-Cream-1.jpg" data-srcset="https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Easy-Yogurt-Cake-Strawberries-and-Cream-1.jpg 680w, https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Easy-Yogurt-Cake-Strawberries-and-Cream-1-227x300.jpg 227w" data-sizes="auto, (max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure></div>


<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Not in a baking mood? This <a href="https://theunlikelybaker.com/refrigerator-cake/"><b>strawberry refrigerator cake</b></a> is for you. Fresh, refreshing, great way to stay cool on a warm sunny day!</span></p>


<div class="wp-block-image">
<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="900" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;680&#039;%20height=&#039;900&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20680%20900&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Strawberry Refrigerator Cake (Strawberry Icebox Cake Filipino Style)" class="wp-image-5341 perfmatters-lazy" data-pin-media="https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Strawberry-Refrigerator-Cake-Filipino-Style-5.jpg" data-src="https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Strawberry-Refrigerator-Cake-Filipino-Style-5.jpg" data-srcset="https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Strawberry-Refrigerator-Cake-Filipino-Style-5.jpg 680w, https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Strawberry-Refrigerator-Cake-Filipino-Style-5-227x300.jpg 227w" data-sizes="auto, (max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure></div>


<p>This <a href="https://www.plattertalk.com/swedish-almond-cake/">almond cake</a> is easy to make and scrumptious too!</p>



<p>And if you want a really easy and simple cake in a jiffy, make this <a href="https://everydaythrifty.com/cake-mix-mug-cake/">cake mix mug cake</a>.</p>



<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Happy baking!</span></p>



<p class="p4"><span class="s5">Did you make this easy recipe for cherry cake? </span><span class="s1">I&rsquo;d love to hear from you in the comments section below.</span></p>


<div id="recipe"></div><div id="wprm-recipe-container-5561" class="wprm-recipe-container" data-recipe-id="5561" data-servings="16"><div class="wprm-recipe wprm-recipe-template-chic-tub"><div class="wprm-container-float-right">
    <div class="wprm-recipe-image wprm-block-image-rounded"><img decoding="async" style="border-width: 0px;border-style: solid;border-color: #666666;border-radius: 3px;" data-pin-nopin="true" width="250" height="250" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;250&#039;%20height=&#039;250&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20250%20250&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" class="attachment-250x250 size-250x250 perfmatters-lazy" alt="Easy Cherry Cake Recipe from Scratch" data-pin-media="https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-Feature.jpg" data-src="https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-Feature-250x250.jpg" data-srcset="https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-Feature-250x250.jpg 250w, https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-Feature-300x300.jpg 300w, https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-Feature-150x150.jpg 150w, https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-Feature-500x500.jpg 500w, https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-Feature-360x360.jpg 360w, https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-Feature-180x180.jpg 180w, https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-Feature-96x96.jpg 96w, https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-Feature-480x480.jpg 480w, https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-Feature-320x320.jpg 320w, https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-Feature-200x200.jpg 200w, https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-Feature-335x335.jpg 335w, https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-Feature-347x347.jpg 347w, https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-Feature-520x520.jpg 520w, https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-Feature-640x640.jpg 640w, https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-Feature-40x40.jpg 40w, https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Cherry-Cake-Recipe-Feature.jpg 680w" data-sizes="auto, (max-width: 250px) 100vw, 250px" /></div>
</div>
<h2 class="wprm-recipe-name wprm-block-text-uppercase"><span id="Easy_Cherry_Cake_Recipe_from_Scratch">Easy Cherry Cake Recipe from Scratch</span></h2>
<div class="wprm-spacer"></div>
<div class="wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-separate wprm-block-text-normal wprm-recipe-author-container" style=""><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label wprm-block-text-normal wprm-recipe-author-label">Author: </span><span class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author wprm-block-text-normal"><a href="https://theunlikelybaker.com/about-me/" target="_blank">Jolina</a></span></div>
<div class="wprm-spacer"></div>
<div class="wprm-recipe-summary wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="p1" style="display: block;">This easy cherry cake recipe is so easy to make and so delicious you&rsquo;d want to bake it all summer long. Dense but soft, not too sweet, bursting with wonderful cherry flavour.</span></div>
