<footer class="entry-footer"></footer></article><h2 class="screen-reader-text">Reader Interactions</h2><div class="entry-comments" id="comments"><h3>Comments</h3><ol class="comment-list">
	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-49524">
	<article id="article-comment-49524">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Malibu</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">July 14, 2025 at 1:29 pm</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p><img class="wprm-comment-rating perfmatters-lazy" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20width=&#039;80&#039;%20height=&#039;16&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%2080%2016&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="5 stars" width="80" height="16" data-src="https://theunlikelybaker.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-recipe-maker/assets/icons/rating/stars-alt-5.svg" /><br />
Excellent (and easy) recipe!  I could not fit anywhere near 1 lb of cherries, and I weighed them prior to pitting.  I wound up using 36 halves.  I am freezing the rest of the halves, so the next time I make this, it will go even faster.  Thank you for a great recipe!</p>
		</div>

